snippet: A single-engine Cessna 12 and a twin-engine Sabreliner that were flying to Brown Field Municipal Airport broke into pieces, leaving no survivors, an official said.
abstract: California officials say collision between two small airplanes near San Diego has left four people dead.
lead_paragraph: A single-engine Cessna 12 and a twin-engine Sabreliner that were flying to Brown Field Municipal Airport broke into pieces, leaving no survivors, an official said.

headline.main: Collision of 2 Small Planes Near a San Diego Airport Kills 4
headline.print_headline: 4 Killed as Small Planes Collide Near a San Diego Airport
